00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:41,910
that's not what I mean.

262
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:43,244
Hear me out.

263
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:44,287
It was me.

264
00:11:44,287 --> 00:11:45,955
I started it all.

265
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:46,998
‐ Huh?

266
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:48,625
‐ I'm the leader of the Dollars.

267
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:50,001
I created them.

268
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:51,836
And I heard what they did
to you and your men.

269
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:55,340
So please,
you can blame me for all of it.

270
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:58,635
And yes, I know I deserve
whatever you want to do to me.

271
00:11:58,635 --> 00:12:00,178
But please, I beg you

272
00:12:00,178 --> 00:12:02,597
not to destroy Ikebukuro
anymore!

273
00:12:02,597 --> 00:12:03,723
Please!

274
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,143
‐ Okay, buddy.

275
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,854
Listen, a man should never
be so quick to grovel.

276
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:12,023
Especially not
in front of a woman.

277
00:12:12,023 --> 00:12:13,566
‐ But I thought‐‐

278
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:15,526
‐ You know,
if I just go and beat up

279
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:18,071
some pathetic kid on the street
in front of my girl,

280
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:21,032
then I'd be the lame one, right?

281
00:12:21,032 --> 00:12:22,784
[chuckles]
And why would I believe

282
00:12:22,784 --> 00:12:24,202
that a plain‐Jane guy like you

283
00:12:24,202 --> 00:12:25,703
is even the leader
of the Dollars

284
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:26,955
in the first place?

285
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:29,123
On the other hand,

286
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:30,500
I don't think you're lying.

287
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,085
‐ Oh.
Well, then.

288
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:35,755
CHIKAGE: But I can't just take
your word for it, right?

289
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:37,298
Whoever founded the Dollars,

290
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:39,801
here's what I know
about that bastard:

291
00:12:39,801 --> 00:12:41,010
he's a freaking lowlife

292
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,720
who gets off
watching on a monitor

293
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,555
as his gang grows on its own

294
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:46,849
and starts fighting
amongst itself.

295
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:50,228
And I just can't imagine a guy
with an honest face like yours

296
00:12:50,228 --> 00:12:51,980
doing something like that.

297
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:54,732
Then again, if you really are

298
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:56,693
the mystery guy
who created the Dollars,

299
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:59,404
why don't you let me give you
a few words of advice?

300
00:12:59,404 --> 00:13:01,489
You should get out of it
while you can.

301
00:13:01,489 --> 00:13:06,494
This thing is way too heavy
a load for a naive kid.

302
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:08,746
You should be living
the ordinary life.

303
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:10,290
Sure, it's not as exciting,

304
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:12,166
but take it
from a lowlife like me,

305
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,085
you'll be happier
in the long run.

306
00:13:14,085 --> 00:13:15,378
No point in forcing yourself

307
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:17,171
to become something
that you're not.

308
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:23,219
MIKADO: When he said all that,

309
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:26,014
did he have any idea
what it would mean to me?

310
00:13:26,014 --> 00:13:30,184
Could he know that his words
would negate my whole being?

311
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:32,895
It wasn't that I was afraid
of being left behind

312
00:13:32,895 --> 00:13:35,273
by the Dollars as they changed.

313
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:37,108
I was afraid
of being left behind

314
00:13:37,108 --> 00:13:39,444
by this city.

315
00:13:39,444 --> 00:13:43,364
In his eyes
and in Shizuo's and Kyohei's,

316
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:46,451
my anguish was nothing
but childish nonsense.

317
00:13:46,451 --> 00:13:49,620
How could the city
leave me behind?

318
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:50,997
The truth is,

319
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:53,958
I never caught up with it
in the first place.

320
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:56,961
[weeping quietly]

321
00:13:56,961 --> 00:14:00,006
<i>[dramatic piano music]</i>

322
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:07,055
<i>♪ ♪</i>

323
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:15,605
SAIKA:
So nobody's online today?

324
00:14:15,605 --> 00:14:16,981
It's lonely.

325
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:19,692
Sorry for saying that.
I'm weird.

326
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:22,528
I'm really sorry.

327
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:25,073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

328
00:14:25,073 --> 00:14:27,784
‐ Huh. So whatever did happen
with all of that?

329
00:14:27,784 --> 00:14:30,495
‐ Well, I'm not so sure myself.

330
00:14:30,495 --> 00:14:31,996
Shinra gave me a call.

331
00:14:31,996 --> 00:14:33,581
Said,
"You've been proven innocent.

332
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:35,166
Everything's okay."

333
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:37,418
‐ That's cool,
but why was the Awakusu group

334
00:14:37,418 --> 00:14:39,128
going after you
in the first place?

335
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:41,422
‐ Well, I'm not at liberty
to talk about that.

336
00:14:41,422 --> 00:14:42,632
‐ Huh?

337
00:14:42,632 --> 00:14:45,176
‐ You see,
Shinra smoothed everything over

338
00:14:45,176 --> 00:14:46,803
with the Awakusu group,

339
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:48,179
but that's only on the condition

340
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:50,515
that I never breathe a word.

341
00:14:50,515 --> 00:14:52,016
‐ Wow.

342
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:55,019
Well, I don't want to get you
in any more trouble.

343
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:56,521
‐ I appreciate that.

344
00:14:56,521 --> 00:14:57,855
SHIKI: You must be happy

345
00:14:57,855 --> 00:15:00,399
that your daughter came back
safely, boss.

346
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:01,275
MIKIYA: Yeah.

347
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:03,236
‐ It was a strange situation.

348
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:06,322
I knew Shizuo Heiwajima
would never kill anyone.

349
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:08,157
From the information
I've received,

350
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:09,534
the person behind this scheme

351
00:15:09,534 --> 00:15:11,077
intended to pin all of the blame

352
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:12,453
on the Asuki Group

353
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:13,830
by using a Russian hit man

354
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:15,540
named Sloan or something.

355
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:17,208
I'm not certain,
but it seems to me

356
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:19,293
the plan was
to give us the upper hand

357
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:21,879
when we met with them
for peace talks.

358
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:24,757
And then Shizuo's involvement
messed it all up.

359
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:26,259
‐ Well, if I had gotten caught,

360
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:28,427
they definitely would've had me
by the balls.

361
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:31,264
I had no choice but to frame him
for the murders.

362
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:33,474
‐ So it was you after all, huh?

363
00:15:33,474 --> 00:15:36,602
‐ Watch it.
Don't say that out loud.

364
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,563
‐ I'm sorry.
You're right.

365
00:15:38,563 --> 00:15:40,314
So these three guys
who were murdered,

366
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:41,357
they were spies?

367
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:42,733
‐ Uh‐huh.
One was a cop

368
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:44,235
and one was from
the Asuki Group,

369
00:15:44,235 --> 00:15:46,821
and I guess
the third was some foreigner.

370
00:15:46,821 --> 00:15:48,865
They never even saw
what hit 'em.

371
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:51,242
‐ Sounds like
a good housecleaning.

372
00:15:51,242 --> 00:15:52,994
MIKIYA:
I don't need your approval.

373
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:54,078
‐ Course not, boss.

374
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:55,872
What about the loose ends?

375
00:15:55,872 --> 00:15:59,500
‐ Akabayashi and Aozaki
are on their way.

376
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,793
<i>♪ ♪</i>

377
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,920
‐ Wait,
they doing it themselves?

378
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:04,255
‐ They said
they wanted to meet up

379
00:16:04,255 --> 00:16:06,424
with their agent
in person first.

380
00:16:06,424 --> 00:16:07,592
When I heard the details,

381
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:09,760
I have to admit
I was pretty surprised.

382
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,887
‐ Huh?

383
00:16:10,887 --> 00:16:13,097
‐ But the way a parent
loves his child

384
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:16,434
is the same everywhere, right?

385
00:16:16,434 --> 00:16:19,770
VARONA: I'd say
I'm 50% good mood and 50% bad.

386
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:21,272
SLOAN: Don't sweat it.

387
00:16:21,272 --> 00:16:24,150
There is still time
to grab that Akane Awakusu,

388
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,943
and that other girl
in the glasses

389
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,403
should be easy prey.

390
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:28,571
VARONA: I suppose.

391
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:30,531
This city is great, isn't it?

392
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:32,200
Once we have this job
out of the way,

393
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,743
I can't wait to treat myself

394
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:36,204
by hunting down the black bike
and that bartender.

395
00:16:36,204 --> 00:16:38,122
That'll be great.
[gulps]

396
00:16:38,122 --> 00:16:40,625
And that is not the only thing
I want to do.

397
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:42,543
I insist we take vacation.

398
00:16:42,543 --> 00:16:43,794
It's necessary.

399
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:45,796
‐ I guess I have no say on this.

400
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:46,964
Not even a veto.

401
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:48,341
AOZAKI: That's right.
‐ Huh?

402
00:16:48,341 --> 00:16:51,677
AOZAKI: You have no veto power.

403
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:54,805
Please allow me
to introduce myself.

404
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:56,015
My name's Aozaki.

405
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,726
I'm sure
you know why I came here.

406
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:00,228
‐ You're Aozaki?

407
00:17:00,228 --> 00:17:02,647
As in the street‐fighting
executive?

408
00:17:02,647 --> 00:17:05,483
‐ You really know your Japanese.
I'm impressed.

409
00:17:05,483 --> 00:17:07,109
‐ Here is what is unimpressive:

410
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:10,154
a big executive of organization
showing up all alone

411
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:12,114
to try and take on
people like us.

412
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:14,659
‐ Come on. Give me
a little more credit than that.

413
00:17:14,659 --> 00:17:17,161
I'm not like that moron
over there.

414
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:19,872
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

415
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:22,875
‐ Pretty harsh, Mr. Aozaki.

416
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,586
There's only one reason
I came up here tonight:

417
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:27,755
'cause I heard
the perp who abducted Akane

418
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:29,340
was a gorgeous foreigner.

419
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:32,426
It's nice to meet you.
The name's Akabayashi.

420
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:35,388
And like that ugly
hatchet‐faced dude over there,

421
00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:38,683
I'm one of the top dogs
of the Awakusu.

422
00:17:38,683 --> 00:17:40,935
‐ And unlike
that moron over there,

423
00:17:40,935 --> 00:17:42,728
I didn't come alone.

424
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:45,565
[gunshots]
‐ [yelling]

425
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:47,608
‐ Sloan!

426
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:48,985
AKABAYASHI: Uh‐uh‐uh.

427
00:17:48,985 --> 00:17:50,695
This is a real treat for me.

428
00:17:50,695 --> 00:17:53,823
I don't often get to dance
with such a pretty young thing.

429
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,493
Level with me.

430
00:17:57,493 --> 00:17:59,370
You're thinking
that the Awakusu group

431
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:01,038
is half‐assed compared to you.

432
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:03,374
I mean, you've been
fighting mercenaries.

433
00:18:03,374 --> 00:18:05,293
Yeah, we know about that.

434
00:18:05,293 --> 00:18:08,546
[chuckles]
I admit you're very strong,

435
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:10,881
but keep in mind,
if you get too carried away,

436
00:18:10,881 --> 00:18:13,009
things will only get
more painful.

437
00:18:14,343 --> 00:18:16,971
Also, if you can get taken down
this easily,

438
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:20,808
going after Shizuo Heiwajima
is nothing but a pipe dream.

439
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:23,185
You can wind up dead,
and believe me,

440
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:25,062
if the daughter
of our new business partner

441
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:28,649
were to get killed on our watch,
we'd have a big problem.

442
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:29,609
Right?

443
00:18:29,609 --> 00:18:32,570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

444
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:35,114
‐ Egor?
‐ [gasps]

445
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:38,075
‐ It's been a long time,
you two.

446
00:18:38,075 --> 00:18:41,037
‐ This gent here
was the one who approached us.

447
00:18:41,037 --> 00:18:43,289
Your old man and the president
of a weapons company

448
00:18:43,289 --> 00:18:47,084
said that in return
for giving us a sweetheart deal,

449
00:18:47,084 --> 00:18:50,630
all I have to do
is pretend I never saw you.

450
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:51,881
<i>♪ ♪</i>

451
00:18:51,881 --> 00:18:53,090
‐ Screw your deal.

452
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:55,259
If you kill Sloan,
you must kill me.

453
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:59,096
To accept such pity as this,
my life would be worthless!

454
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:00,598
‐ [laughs]
You don't know

455
00:19:00,598 --> 00:19:02,975
what you're talking about.

456
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,435
Good night.

457
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:07,146
‐ Varon‐‐
[grunts]

458
00:19:08,981 --> 00:19:10,775
‐ [grunts]
I suppose we can do

459
00:19:10,775 --> 00:19:14,945
whatever we want
to this poor bastard, right?

460
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:17,823
‐ Sorry we missed the fun,
Captain Akabayashi,

461
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:19,950
but you can leave the rest
to us.

462
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:21,869
‐ I was counting on that.

463
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:24,413
A cute one like this
killing herself‐‐

464
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:25,956
I don't think
I could sleep at night,

465
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,208
if you know what I mean.

466
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:29,418
‐ Nothing to worry about,
Akabayashi.

467
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:32,713
When you can't sleep, I'll tell
what best thing for you is.

468
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:34,256
You've got to eat some shark.

469
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:36,300
I'll get you the best there is

470
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:39,345
and shark fin soup too.

471
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:40,554
‐ Thanks.

472
00:19:40,554 --> 00:19:43,599
I'll be sure
to stop by sometime.

473
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:45,393
‐ Okay.
Let's go.

474
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:50,398
MAN: [speaking foreign language]

475
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:04,161
‐ So, Mikado, what did you want
to talk to me about?

476
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:07,873
‐ Well, I've been thinking
long and hard about the Dollars

477
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:09,792
and how things currently are,

478
00:20:09,792 --> 00:20:11,836
and it's just not right.

479
00:20:11,836 --> 00:20:15,297
It's not what I had in mind
when I first started this group,

480
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:16,966
but the Dollars
don't have rules,

481
00:20:16,966 --> 00:20:18,676
so the moment I make rules,

482
00:20:18,676 --> 00:20:20,386
they won't be the Dollars.

483
00:20:20,386 --> 00:20:24,515
In order to get what you want
in a world without any rules,

484
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:26,183
you need to have power.

485
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:28,853
That said,

486
00:20:28,853 --> 00:20:30,229
if you still would like
to help me

487
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,564
get that kind of power,

488
00:20:31,564 --> 00:20:33,357
and if you really think
I can still be of use

489
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:34,859
to the Blue Squares,

490
00:20:34,859 --> 00:20:37,111
then I'll take
the deal you're offering.

491
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:38,904
‐ Hey, that's awesome!

492
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:41,365
‐ Come on over here

493
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:43,200
and I'll draw up a contract
real quick.

494
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,410
‐ A contract?

495
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:45,995
‐ If you and I
are gonna make a deal,

496
00:20:45,995 --> 00:20:47,705
then it's only right
to put it in writing

497
00:20:47,705 --> 00:20:49,081
and make it official.

498
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:53,085
‐ Huh?

499
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,503
[yells]

500
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:56,130
‐ Dude!
Aoba, you okay?

501
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:58,090
‐ Hey, what the hell
are you doing?

502
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:02,261
‐ Mikado...

503
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:03,721
tell me...

504
00:21:03,721 --> 00:21:04,972
what's going on.

505
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:06,724
‐ I don't know why you did it,

506
00:21:06,724 --> 00:21:09,351
but you dragged Anri into this.

507
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:11,353
You're getting what you deserve.

508
00:21:11,353 --> 00:21:15,065
This is the very first order
I'm giving as your leader.

509
00:21:15,065 --> 00:21:16,942
You will accept my anger.

510
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:19,779
‐ [exclaims]

511
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:21,363
I accept that

512
00:21:21,363 --> 00:21:22,948
and this too.

513
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:26,577
This bloody piece of paper
is our contract.

514
00:21:26,577 --> 00:21:28,704
And as of today, Mikado,

515
00:21:28,704 --> 00:21:30,664
you're leader
of the Blue Squares.

516
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:32,958
We're your pawns
to use as you wish.

517
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,251
With us under your command,

518
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:36,587
you can lead the Dollars
down any path.

519
00:21:36,587 --> 00:21:37,505
‐ Really?

520
00:21:37,505 --> 00:21:39,507
[sighs]
That's great.

521
00:21:39,507 --> 00:21:42,259
I'm so glad you're okay with it.

522
00:21:42,259 --> 00:21:44,428
And I'm really sorry
about your hand.

523
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:47,681
Oh, I brought some bandages
and antiseptic with me.

524
00:21:47,681 --> 00:21:49,767
Let me take care of that
for you.

525
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:51,185
Now, make sure you keep your
hand...

526
00:21:51,185 --> 00:21:52,937
There's no going back now,

527
00:21:52,937 --> 00:21:57,107
but surprisingly,
I don't feel any regrets.

528
00:21:57,107 --> 00:21:59,318
I'm gonna do what I can
to return the Dollars

529
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:01,445
to what they should be.

530
00:22:01,445 --> 00:22:02,696
If I can do that,

531
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:03,948
I can hold my head up high

532
00:22:03,948 --> 00:22:06,325
when I face Anri and Masaomi.

533
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:09,245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

534
00:22:09,245 --> 00:22:10,788
Sorry, Masaomi.

535
00:22:10,788 --> 00:22:13,457
You warned me
to stay away from the Dollars,

536
00:22:13,457 --> 00:22:16,293
but I couldn't do it.

537
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:17,294
I'm sorry.

538
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:19,463
<i>♪ ♪</i>

539
00:22:19,463 --> 00:22:20,756
I'm sorry.

540
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:23,801
IZAYA: Yes, that's fine.

541
00:22:23,801 --> 00:22:25,886
Right.
I understand.

542
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:28,472
I really believe the Asuki Group
is the best outfit

543
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:31,016
to run Ikebukuro,
that's all.

544
00:22:31,016 --> 00:22:34,937
And I hope
for your continued support.

545
00:22:34,937 --> 00:22:37,940
Looks like I resolved that issue
in just a day.

546
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:41,318
[cell phone vibrating]

547
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:42,820
JINNAI: Oh.
Hello.

548
00:22:42,820 --> 00:22:45,781
Is this Mr. Izaya Orihara
I'm speaking with?

549
00:22:45,781 --> 00:22:47,408
‐ Yes, this is Orihara.

550
00:22:47,408 --> 00:22:50,494
JINNAI: I have to tell you,
I'm at the end of my rope here,

551
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,663
thanks to you getting
that monster mixed up

552
00:22:52,663 --> 00:22:54,456
with the Awakusu Group.

553
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:57,084
It's really thrown me
off my game plan.

554
00:22:57,084 --> 00:22:59,295
Seriously, if Akane Awakusu

555
00:22:59,295 --> 00:23:02,423
hadn't gotten involved
with Shizuo Heiwajima,

556
00:23:02,423 --> 00:23:05,175
things would've gone
much more smoothly by now.

557
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:06,594
‐ Hey, who the hell is this?

558
00:23:06,594 --> 00:23:09,513
JINNAI: [laughs]
No need for you to know my name.

559
00:23:09,513 --> 00:23:11,140
But as a token
of our new friendship,

560
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:12,808
let me offer an opinion...

561
00:23:12,808 --> 00:23:15,603
or rather, a warning.

562
00:23:15,603 --> 00:23:18,522
You're a bit too good‐looking,
Izaya.

563
00:23:18,522 --> 00:23:19,690
‐ What?

564
00:23:19,690 --> 00:23:21,025
JINNAI: It makes you stand out

565
00:23:21,025 --> 00:23:22,318
in a crowd,

566
00:23:22,318 --> 00:23:24,111
so in your case,
trying to blend in

567
00:23:24,111 --> 00:23:27,114
really isn't an ideal way
for you to hide.

568
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:30,743
Besides,
you're looking kind of stressed.

569
00:23:30,743 --> 00:23:33,662
I think a nap
would do you a world of good.

570
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:34,622
[thud]

571
00:23:34,622 --> 00:23:35,706
[Izaya grunts]

572
00:23:39,376 --> 00:23:40,377
MAN: Whoa.

573
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:41,921
WOMAN: Is he okay?

574
00:23:41,921 --> 00:23:43,047
Just fell over.

575
00:23:43,047 --> 00:23:45,549
JINNAI: Oh, and since you asked,

576
00:23:45,549 --> 00:23:47,885
my name is Jinnai Yodogiri,

577
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:51,347
and I'm pleased
to make your acquaintance.

578
00:23:51,347 --> 00:23:52,765
‐ Damn.

579
00:23:52,765 --> 00:23:54,892
I underestimated them.

580
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:59,939
<i>[freewheeling jazz music]</i>

581
00:23:59,939 --> 00:24:06,946
<i>♪ ♪</i>

